      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JUST AS WELL NZ (1) has been good from wider barriers of late, working but digging deep to miss a by a nose two back at Shepparton before leading and sticking on to be beaten less than 4m here last time. Should enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Winning chance. RACHELS LEGACY (3) is reliable filly who continued her good form with a 3.7m second from the back row at this circuit and distance last week. Came from a wide barrier for fourth in the Nutrien Classic Final at Listed level prior. Should get her chance from this draw. SHEER VITALITY (9) draws for a trail and comes right into contention after he led and fought well to score by a head at this circuit and distance last time out. FOURTH RESPONSE (7) draws wide but has won a trial since last seen and hasn't missed a place in six starts here, winning twice.",
